===Etymology===
From [[Hindi]] ''[[बॅँगला]]'' or ''[[बंगला]]'' (''ba.ngalā'') via the [[Gujarati]] ''[[bungalo]]'', meaning ''one-story house''.

===Noun===
'''bungalow'''
#A small [[house]] or [[cottage]] usually having a [[single]] [[story]]
#A [[thatched]] or [[tile]]d one-story house in [[India]] surrounded by a wide [[verandah]]
